  "commentary": "With SPX at 6996.95 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (19.7B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they hedge their long gamma exposure in PIN regime. The thick positive gamma structure from 7000-7100 creates a strong ceiling effect, while the flip at 6874 provides downside support - current positioning suggests dealers will fade moves in either direction to keep price rangebound.\n\nKey levels: 7000 is the critical resistance where dealer selling intensifies, 6874 flip strike marks where hedging dynamics reverse, and the 6800 negative gamma pocket could accelerate any breakdown below the flip.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get capped near 7000 and grind sideways between 6875-7000.",
